00:00:06.448 --> 00:00:10.416
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:12.910 --> 00:00:14.660
JONATHAN BERENT: Good
afternoon, everyone.

00:00:14.660 --> 00:00:17.310
My name is Jonathan Berent,
and I'll be your host today.

00:00:17.310 --> 00:00:18.800
Thank you so much for coming.

00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:22.830
Thanks to those that are on
the livestream today as well.

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:25.530
We live in dynamic times.

00:00:25.530 --> 00:00:28.760
Never before has a generation
been so assaulted by the images

00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:31.310
from the media, stories
from the internet

00:00:31.310 --> 00:00:34.960
that seem to touch a
nerve in us personally.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:39.230
Seems like every week, whether
you are black or white,

00:00:39.230 --> 00:00:42.030
straight or gay, from
a rich background

00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:44.110
or a poor background,
there's a story

00:00:44.110 --> 00:00:47.820
that elicits a reaction in us.

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:49.120
But there is hope.

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:52.590
As long as the human spirit
is alive on this planet,

00:00:52.590 --> 00:00:54.390
there will always be hope.

00:00:54.390 --> 00:00:58.100
We only have to think of names
like Mahatma Gandhi or Mother

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:02.570
Teresa, now Saint Teresa, Anne
Frank or Martin Luther King,

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:06.250
to know that it just takes a
single, passionate individual

00:01:06.250 --> 00:01:08.270
who has the courage to
risk it all to bring

00:01:08.270 --> 00:01:11.190
the light into this world.

00:01:11.190 --> 00:01:13.990
If you would, picture one of
their iconic faces in your mind

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:14.780
right now.

00:01:14.780 --> 00:01:15.940
Just take a moment.

00:01:15.940 --> 00:01:18.470
Bring one to mind.

00:01:18.470 --> 00:01:21.810
What do you notice inside?

00:01:21.810 --> 00:01:27.580
Is it courage,
inspiration, love?

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:30.230
Before them, there had been
numerous beacons of change

00:01:30.230 --> 00:01:33.250
that have walked from
all walks of life.

00:01:33.250 --> 00:01:37.070
Milarepa was a Tibetan monk
who was very revengeful

00:01:37.070 --> 00:01:39.060
in his youth, but
then he became one

00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:43.860
of Tibet's most loved and
cherished figures of history.

00:01:43.860 --> 00:01:47.930
Saint Francis of Assisi was
a rich, disillusion young man

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:52.470
who left it all to pursue a life
of compassion and generosity

00:01:52.470 --> 00:01:54.900
towards everyone.

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:58.220
The prophet Muhammad was
also born into a noble family

00:01:58.220 --> 00:02:03.620
and grew up to be rich but
then turned contemplative.

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:07.080
What these three individuals
have in common is they

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:10.520
all had the courage to
do the inner work first

00:02:10.520 --> 00:02:14.000
before they brought
outer change.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.890
Let's stop there for a minute.

00:02:15.890 --> 00:02:17.710
Speaking of inner
work, how many of you

00:02:17.710 --> 00:02:20.150
might have had a little
twinge of emotion

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:23.430
when I said one of these names?

00:02:23.430 --> 00:02:24.362
Why?

00:02:24.362 --> 00:02:26.070
Well, these names,
these last three ones,

00:02:26.070 --> 00:02:28.048
are associated with
world religions.

00:02:28.048 --> 00:02:30.672
And some of these religions have
been associated with violence.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:35.710
We're not talking
about religion today.

00:02:35.710 --> 00:02:38.770
We're not talking about
spirituality today.

00:02:38.770 --> 00:02:41.340
You can all breathe
a sigh of relief.

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:44.790
We are talking about taking a
moment to reflect on the times

00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:48.190
that we live in and what
they require of us, what they

00:02:48.190 --> 00:02:51.460
require of us as an individuals
and what they require

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:54.730
of us as a company, one of
the most influential companies

00:02:54.730 --> 00:02:56.730
on the planet.

00:02:56.730 --> 00:02:58.230
If you felt a twinge
of emotion when

00:02:58.230 --> 00:03:01.280
I mentioned one of these names
or even the word "religion,"

00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:02.630
that's normal.

00:03:02.630 --> 00:03:05.310
If you feel outraged by
the things you see on TV

00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:08.936
or read in the
newspaper, that's normal.

00:03:08.936 --> 00:03:11.310
If you have passionate feelings
about the election that's

00:03:11.310 --> 00:03:13.219
coming up in a
month, that's normal.

00:03:13.219 --> 00:03:15.760
In fact, if you don't have some
of those passionate feelings,

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:16.843
I'd say that's not normal.

00:03:16.843 --> 00:03:18.118
[LAUGHTER]

00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:23.910
However, we have to learn
to deal with these emotions.

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:25.400
We have to learn
to find ways that

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:29.640
integrate our thoughts and our
emotions more constructively

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:33.090
so we can more skillfully
navigate these dynamic times

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:35.870
so we can have impact.

00:03:35.870 --> 00:03:39.250
Today we hope to give you both
the permission and the tools

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:40.900
to do just that.

00:03:40.900 --> 00:03:44.740
Sadhguru is a realized
yogi and mystic.

00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:48.380
He's a man whose passion spills
into everything he touches,

00:03:48.380 --> 00:03:51.250
including, I learned
yesterday, golf.

00:03:51.250 --> 00:03:53.390
With a keen mind and
an unbounded heart,

00:03:53.390 --> 00:03:55.239
his presence alone
gives you a taste

00:03:55.239 --> 00:03:56.780
of what the natural
state of the mind

00:03:56.780 --> 00:04:01.394
can experience in terms of
love and joy and freedom.

00:04:01.394 --> 00:04:03.060
Sadhguru's vision to
transform the world

00:04:03.060 --> 00:04:05.567
has been unfolding
over the last 30 years.

00:04:05.567 --> 00:04:07.150
The Isha Foundation,
which he started,

00:04:07.150 --> 00:04:10.480
has numerous programs to
promote inclusive culture

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:12.640
and establish global harmony.

00:04:12.640 --> 00:04:17.880
Named one of India's 50 most
influential individuals,

00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.300
he has deeply touched the
lives of millions worldwide.

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:22.570
He has spoken at forums
like the United Nations

00:04:22.570 --> 00:04:24.370
and humble villages
throughout India.

00:04:24.370 --> 00:04:27.510
He's equally known for his
transformational yoga programs,

00:04:27.510 --> 00:04:30.910
as well as his large-scale
social projects.

00:04:30.910 --> 00:04:34.290
The projects address things
like quality education

00:04:34.290 --> 00:04:37.730
for the poor, environmental
stewardship, holistic health,

00:04:37.730 --> 00:04:40.210
peace, and well-being.

00:04:40.210 --> 00:04:45.030
Sadhguru says joy is our
nature, misery our own making.

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:47.720
This is a provocative
statement that he addresses

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:50.240
in his new book, "Inner
Engineering, a Yogi's Guide

00:04:50.240 --> 00:04:52.400
to Joy," which there will
be a few copies for sale

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:54.551
in the back.

00:04:54.551 --> 00:04:55.051
Sadhguru.

