00:39:31.060 --> 00:39:34.010
would not enter your life
and will not enter your life.

00:39:34.010 --> 00:39:37.390
So turning inward is
not a survival process.

00:39:37.390 --> 00:39:40.710
So there are two fundamental
dimensions within you,

00:39:40.710 --> 00:39:44.920
instinct of self-preservation,
longing to expand limitlessly.

00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:46.880
Both true for a human being.

00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:49.740
This is essentially a human
problem on the planet.

00:39:49.740 --> 00:39:52.370
No other creator wants
to expand limitlessly.

00:39:52.370 --> 00:39:54.330
They are only
thinking of survival.

00:39:54.330 --> 00:39:56.270
Their stomach
full, life settled.

00:39:56.270 --> 00:39:58.850
For you, stomach empty,
only one problem.

00:39:58.850 --> 00:40:00.346
Stomach full, 100 problems.

00:40:00.346 --> 00:40:02.090
[LAUGHTER]

00:40:02.090 --> 00:40:07.560
Yes, so all your trouble
begins after stomach gets full,

00:40:07.560 --> 00:40:08.400
isn't it?

00:40:08.400 --> 00:40:12.240
Because this is longing
to expand limitlessly.

00:40:12.240 --> 00:40:15.130
In the evolutionary
process, we can say this.

00:40:15.130 --> 00:40:18.860
But every other creature,
nature has drawn two lines

00:40:18.860 --> 00:40:21.120
within which they live and die.

00:40:21.120 --> 00:40:22.550
They're quite final.

00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:25.570
But once you become human,
there is only a bottom line.

00:40:25.570 --> 00:40:27.310
There is no top line.

00:40:27.310 --> 00:40:29.850
So what humanity is
suffering and confused

00:40:29.850 --> 00:40:31.820
about is not their bondage.

00:40:31.820 --> 00:40:34.850
They're suffering their freedom.

00:40:34.850 --> 00:40:36.636
What do you do with that?

00:40:36.636 --> 00:40:39.600
[CHUCKLING]

00:40:39.600 --> 00:40:40.600
JONATHAN BERENT: Wow.

00:40:40.600 --> 00:40:42.650
All right, well, I'm
going to invite anyone--

00:40:42.650 --> 00:40:46.060
SADHGURU: All these identities
of religion, race, caste,

00:40:46.060 --> 00:40:49.020
creed, nationality
is they're trying

00:40:49.020 --> 00:40:51.300
to set their own bondage.

00:40:51.300 --> 00:40:54.900
Because no bondage has been
given to you by nature.

00:40:54.900 --> 00:40:57.860
You're trying to set
your own bondage so

00:40:57.860 --> 00:41:01.310
that you feel secure somehow.

00:41:01.310 --> 00:41:03.810
JONATHAN BERENT: And so that's
part of the motivation that's

00:41:03.810 --> 00:41:05.300
driving the attacks.

00:41:05.300 --> 00:41:07.900
SADHGURU: All these
identities, being identified

00:41:07.900 --> 00:41:10.370
with the color of your
skin, with whatever nonsense

00:41:10.370 --> 00:41:15.690
you believe in and nationality--
just a cloth, a flag.

00:41:15.690 --> 00:41:19.190
People will stand there and
tears will come to them.

00:41:19.190 --> 00:41:20.510
Just look at that.

00:41:20.510 --> 00:41:22.590
It really amazes me.

00:41:22.590 --> 00:41:25.110
And on one level,
it's beautiful.

00:41:25.110 --> 00:41:26.840
On another level,
it's super ugly

00:41:26.840 --> 00:41:30.380
that you get identified with
all these kind of things.

00:41:30.380 --> 00:41:33.740
People get identified with
a symbol, with a word,

00:41:33.740 --> 00:41:36.540
with just about
anything, all right?

00:41:36.540 --> 00:41:39.600
So you are trying to create
some artificial boundary

00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:40.450
of your own.

00:41:40.450 --> 00:41:43.680
Once you create this boundary
and you have another boundary,

00:41:43.680 --> 00:41:46.180
I have my boundary, when
they meet, we clash.

00:41:54.059 --> 00:41:55.850
JONATHAN BERENT: So if
you have a question,

00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:57.730
please go ahead and
come to the mic.

00:41:57.730 --> 00:42:01.800
And again, we're trying
to think about this topic

00:42:01.800 --> 00:42:03.390
of inclusive consciousness.

00:42:03.390 --> 00:42:05.590
You've heard a lot of
things shared from our VPs

00:42:05.590 --> 00:42:07.630
and also from this conversation.

00:42:07.630 --> 00:42:10.390
So let's hear what's on
your mind based on all this.

00:42:10.390 --> 00:42:11.844
Over here.

00:42:11.844 --> 00:42:12.510
AUDIENCE: Hello.

00:42:12.510 --> 00:42:19.230
So I'm involved in organizing
a peace conference in India.

00:42:19.230 --> 00:42:21.770
And it's a very
grassroots-led effort,

00:42:21.770 --> 00:42:25.010
so no politicians, thank God.

00:42:25.010 --> 00:42:28.310
And I found it interesting
that you said you stopped

00:42:28.310 --> 00:42:29.900
attending peace conferences.

00:42:29.900 --> 00:42:34.000
So I'd love to hear from you
any advice on what we should do

00:42:34.000 --> 00:42:37.090
or what we should avoid
to make this small effort

00:42:37.090 --> 00:42:39.980
a success for the people
who are attending.

00:42:39.980 --> 00:42:44.840
SADHGURU: See, when you say,
no politicians, thank God,

00:42:44.840 --> 00:42:48.820
you're just not attending
to the source of problems.

00:42:48.820 --> 00:42:56.170
[LAUGHTER]

00:42:56.170 --> 00:42:58.825
Politicians are not
another breed of people.

00:43:01.720 --> 00:43:04.960
A democratic society
means tomorrow you

00:43:04.960 --> 00:43:06.730
may become the president
of this nation.

00:43:06.730 --> 00:43:09.820
That's what it means, yes?

00:43:09.820 --> 00:43:13.770
If you're willing to
stick your neck out,

00:43:13.770 --> 00:43:15.990
you may become the
president of this country

00:43:15.990 --> 00:43:19.180
or a prime minister
of another country.

00:43:19.180 --> 00:43:21.550
So a politician did
not drop from the sky.

00:43:21.550 --> 00:43:23.850
He is not some other creature.

00:43:23.850 --> 00:43:25.600
He is just like you and me.

00:43:25.600 --> 00:43:28.760
He stuck his neck out, which you
and me are not willing to do.

00:43:28.760 --> 00:43:30.710
Let's admit this.

00:43:30.710 --> 00:43:32.700
It's not an easy thing.

00:43:32.700 --> 00:43:34.780
It's easy to sit
down and comment,

00:43:34.780 --> 00:43:39.350
but it's not an easy thing
to try to run a nation.

00:43:39.350 --> 00:43:43.780
It's complex, believe me.

00:43:43.780 --> 00:43:47.740
So you must have politicians.

00:43:47.740 --> 00:43:50.310
But you must have
am atmosphere where

00:43:50.310 --> 00:43:53.330
it's not political in
nature, where they will also

00:43:53.330 --> 00:43:56.210
let their hair down and
talk like common citizens

00:43:56.210 --> 00:43:57.070
or human beings.

00:43:57.070 --> 00:44:00.110
But without them, what
are you going to change?

00:44:00.110 --> 00:44:02.690
So peace conferences, if
it's just an entertainment,

00:44:02.690 --> 00:44:06.760
you can gather your friends
and have a peace conference.

00:44:06.760 --> 00:44:09.550
But if you want peace on the
planet, the most important

00:44:09.550 --> 00:44:12.860
politicians, the most powerful
politicians in this world

00:44:12.860 --> 00:44:13.720
must be there.

00:44:13.720 --> 00:44:17.280
Only then there is a
possibility of peace, isn't it?

00:44:17.280 --> 00:44:18.890
Otherwise it's
just entertainment.

00:44:18.890 --> 00:44:19.520
I'll tell you.

00:44:19.520 --> 00:44:21.960
I was in a very important
peace conference.

00:44:21.960 --> 00:44:29.110
There were 42 Nobel laureates,
each one of them pulling out

00:44:29.110 --> 00:44:35.130
10, 20, one of them 44, 45 pages
of printed sheets without even

00:44:35.130 --> 00:44:38.480
looking up at anybody, just went
on reading their paid speeches

00:44:38.480 --> 00:44:41.470
from morning to evening.

00:44:41.470 --> 00:44:43.820
And slowly, the hall
was becoming peaceful.

00:44:43.820 --> 00:44:47.816
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:50.800 --> 00:44:54.350
In one afternoon, the
second day afternoon,

00:44:54.350 --> 00:44:58.340
I'm sitting right here in the
front row, and I look around.

00:44:58.340 --> 00:45:01.500
Literally everybody has fallen
asleep except the security

00:45:01.500 --> 00:45:04.790
man who was standing there
and me, the idiot, who

00:45:04.790 --> 00:45:06.314
is sitting up
there and believing

00:45:06.314 --> 00:45:08.730
there's going to be world peace
because of this conference

00:45:08.730 --> 00:45:12.640
and sitting up there, alert,
listening to every word.

00:45:12.640 --> 00:45:13.670
Then I looked around.

00:45:13.670 --> 00:45:15.910
Everybody's become
very peaceful.

00:45:15.910 --> 00:45:18.740
They've been having
late-night parties,

00:45:18.740 --> 00:45:20.580
and they're all very peaceful.

00:45:20.580 --> 00:45:24.320
Then when my turn to
speak came, I said, see,

00:45:24.320 --> 00:45:28.700
I've heard so much
peace [INAUDIBLE] today.

00:45:28.700 --> 00:45:33.740
I want to ask you, can
all of you or any of you

00:45:33.740 --> 00:45:35.890
put your hand on
your heart and say

00:45:35.890 --> 00:45:40.077
you are genuinely
peaceful in your life?

00:45:40.077 --> 00:45:41.160
They were straight enough.

00:45:41.160 --> 00:45:44.480
They said, no, we
are not peaceful.

00:45:44.480 --> 00:45:47.740
I said, if you cannot
make your mind peaceful,

00:45:47.740 --> 00:45:51.170
how the hell are you going
to make the world peaceful?

00:45:51.170 --> 00:45:53.340
What's happening in
the world is just

00:45:53.340 --> 00:45:56.190
a larger manifestation of
the nonsense that's happening

00:45:56.190 --> 00:45:58.730
in our heads, isn't it?

00:45:58.730 --> 00:46:01.680
If you and me were truly
peaceful human beings,

00:46:01.680 --> 00:46:05.650
do we have to worry about
you and me fighting someday?

00:46:05.650 --> 00:46:06.610
Hello?

00:46:06.610 --> 00:46:10.600
Whatever the issues, we'll
sit down and handle it, right?

00:46:10.600 --> 00:46:13.670
Because there is violence in us,
now we have to have a boundary.

00:46:13.670 --> 00:46:18.065
Here there's a barricade
just in case I get violent

00:46:18.065 --> 00:46:19.270
or you get violent.

00:46:19.270 --> 00:46:23.206
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:26.650 --> 00:46:29.806
JONATHAN BERENT: How about
from this side over there.

00:46:33.549 --> 00:46:34.090
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:46:34.090 --> 00:46:36.200
Just a very basic
question-- you mentioned

00:46:36.200 --> 00:46:39.120
that before we start
educational of our children,

00:46:39.120 --> 00:46:42.990
we should try and make sure that
their identity is the cosmos.

00:46:42.990 --> 00:46:44.960
But how do you do
that then we ourselves

00:46:44.960 --> 00:46:47.350
are so hard-wired--
I mean, how do we

00:46:47.350 --> 00:46:50.050
tell our children that
their identity is more

00:46:50.050 --> 00:46:52.490
when my own thinking
is so limited, when

00:46:52.490 --> 00:46:54.630
in my own identity
is so limited?

00:46:54.630 --> 00:46:57.610
How do I pass something
like that to a child

00:46:57.610 --> 00:47:01.000
when I am not capable
of doing that myself?

00:47:01.000 --> 00:47:03.194
SADHGURU: Anyway, whatever
you tell your children,

00:47:03.194 --> 00:47:05.110
your children don't
listen to you [INAUDIBLE].

00:47:05.110 --> 00:47:07.440
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:07.440 --> 00:47:10.790
If you have them on the way, I'm
telling you, forewarning you.

00:47:10.790 --> 00:47:13.070
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:13.070 --> 00:47:16.090
They don't listen to a
damn thing that you say.

00:47:16.090 --> 00:47:19.310
But they observe you.

00:47:19.310 --> 00:47:23.800
They pick up things from
the way you are behaving.

00:47:23.800 --> 00:47:26.930
If you don't show
that in your life,

00:47:26.930 --> 00:47:31.250
your teachings will be
hated after some time.

00:47:31.250 --> 00:47:32.660
Yes.

00:47:32.660 --> 00:47:35.180
See, this is most unfortunate.

00:47:35.180 --> 00:47:39.320
I just see this happening
to so many people.

00:47:39.320 --> 00:47:41.800
When they have a
child, these parents,

00:47:41.800 --> 00:47:43.660
they did everything
possible to the child.

00:47:43.660 --> 00:47:46.900
They thought this
is their life, not

00:47:46.900 --> 00:47:51.420
just changing diapers, so many
things, everything possible.

00:47:51.420 --> 00:47:53.440
They taught they're
living for this person.

00:47:53.440 --> 00:47:58.320
As this person becomes bigger
and in their over-concern

00:47:58.320 --> 00:48:00.145
about how this child
should be, trying

00:48:00.145 --> 00:48:03.640
to teach him the best things
in the universe, which is not

00:48:03.640 --> 00:48:07.390
true in their lives, slowly
you will see by the time

00:48:07.390 --> 00:48:12.260
he becomes a teenager,
he avoids them.

00:48:12.260 --> 00:48:15.200
If he wants to share
something, if he

00:48:15.200 --> 00:48:17.850
wants to listen to some
sense, he goes to his friends,

00:48:17.850 --> 00:48:19.390
never to his parents.

00:48:19.390 --> 00:48:23.350
Not everybody, I'm saying,
but largely it is happening.

00:48:23.350 --> 00:48:26.670
Because they don't make sense.

00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:28.700
They talk things that
doesn't make sense.

00:48:28.700 --> 00:48:32.610
People keep asking me, Sadhguru,
how did you become like this?

00:48:32.610 --> 00:48:33.680
What is this [INAUDIBLE]?

00:48:33.680 --> 00:48:37.010
Did you display your life
and you are like this?

00:48:37.010 --> 00:48:38.530
This is all I did.

00:48:38.530 --> 00:48:41.850
I strived to remain uneducated.

00:48:41.850 --> 00:48:43.500
It's not easy, believe me.

00:48:43.500 --> 00:48:47.180
From the day you are born,
just everybody around you

00:48:47.180 --> 00:48:49.170
is trying to teach
you something that

00:48:49.170 --> 00:48:50.669
did not work in their life.

00:48:50.669 --> 00:48:55.070
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:55.070 --> 00:48:57.859
You can clearly see it's
not worked in their life.

00:48:57.859 --> 00:48:59.400
Because if it had
worked, they should

00:48:59.400 --> 00:49:01.950
have been joyful and ecstatic.

00:49:01.950 --> 00:49:02.860
It's not worked.

00:49:02.860 --> 00:49:04.310
They've become long-faced.

00:49:04.310 --> 00:49:07.140
But they're teaching you
all kinds of best things,

00:49:07.140 --> 00:49:09.140
louder universe.

00:49:09.140 --> 00:49:10.670
It's not going to work.

00:49:10.670 --> 00:49:13.164
You don't have to say a word.

00:49:13.164 --> 00:49:15.330
I will tell you-- is it OK
if I can share something?

00:49:15.330 --> 00:49:16.246
JONATHAN BERENT: Sure.

00:49:18.220 --> 00:49:21.870
SADHGURU: I brought
up my girl alone.

00:49:21.870 --> 00:49:24.850
At the age of seven,
she lost her mother.

00:49:24.850 --> 00:49:29.510
So one rule I put-- she's been
traveling with me since she's

00:49:29.510 --> 00:49:32.400
4 and 1/2 years of age, OK?

00:49:32.400 --> 00:49:36.170
I'm sorry since she is 4
and 1/2 months, not years.

00:49:36.170 --> 00:49:39.880
4 and 1/2, I sent her to school.

00:49:39.880 --> 00:49:43.220
But as a little infant,
she traveled with me.

00:49:43.220 --> 00:49:44.462
And I made one rule.

00:49:44.462 --> 00:49:46.920
Where ever I went, I always
stayed with many, many families

00:49:46.920 --> 00:49:48.310
all over the country.

00:49:48.310 --> 00:49:50.150
I always told
everybody, never teach

00:49:50.150 --> 00:49:56.390
her anything, no ABC, no 1,
2, 3, no rhyme, nor nonsense.

00:49:56.390 --> 00:49:58.904
I don't want anybody
to teach her anything.

00:49:58.904 --> 00:50:00.820
People thought this is
strange or [INAUDIBLE].

00:50:00.820 --> 00:50:02.730
And I said, just leave her.

00:50:02.730 --> 00:50:04.710
By the time she
was 18 months, she

00:50:04.710 --> 00:50:06.839
was speaking three
languages fluently

00:50:06.839 --> 00:50:08.130
because nobody messed with her.

00:50:08.130 --> 00:50:10.080
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:10.080 --> 00:50:12.740
And she grew up joyfully,
went to school, everything.

00:50:12.740 --> 00:50:16.672
At the age of 13, something
she was disturbed at school,

00:50:16.672 --> 00:50:17.630
and she came back home.

00:50:17.630 --> 00:50:20.420
And one day she said,
you're teaching everybody

00:50:20.420 --> 00:50:21.150
so many things.

00:50:21.150 --> 00:50:23.450
You're not telling me anything.

00:50:23.450 --> 00:50:26.292
I said, well, I don't
do anything unsolicited.

00:50:26.292 --> 00:50:28.860
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:28.860 --> 00:50:29.895
I've been waiting.

00:50:29.895 --> 00:50:30.520
It's all right.

00:50:30.520 --> 00:50:31.820
Now you come.

00:50:31.820 --> 00:50:34.680
There's only one thing
you need to know.

00:50:34.680 --> 00:50:36.542
I said, never to
look up to anybody.

00:50:36.542 --> 00:50:38.000
She looked at me,
"what about you?"

00:50:38.000 --> 00:50:39.750
kind of thing in her face.

00:50:39.750 --> 00:50:41.580
I said, not even me.

00:50:41.580 --> 00:50:43.310
Never look up to anybody.

00:50:43.310 --> 00:50:44.700
Never look down on anybody.

00:50:44.700 --> 00:50:47.100
That's how you have
to do with life.

00:50:47.100 --> 00:50:49.690
Never look up to
anything or anybody.

00:50:49.690 --> 00:50:52.250
Never look down on
anything or anybody.

00:50:52.250 --> 00:50:56.480
Suddenly you will see
life just the way it is.

00:50:56.480 --> 00:50:59.640
Right now, something is
high, something is low,

00:50:59.640 --> 00:51:02.450
something is God, something
is devil, something is virtue,

00:51:02.450 --> 00:51:03.510
something is sin.

00:51:03.510 --> 00:51:06.040
You divided the universe in
a million different ways,

00:51:06.040 --> 00:51:07.560
and then you're
trying to fix it.

00:51:07.560 --> 00:51:09.150
It's not going to work.

00:51:09.150 --> 00:51:13.430
The instrument which broke
the world into pieces

00:51:13.430 --> 00:51:14.950
is your intellect.

00:51:14.950 --> 00:51:17.590
With that, you're trying
to fix everything.

00:51:17.590 --> 00:51:20.260
It's not going to work.

00:51:20.260 --> 00:51:23.730
Now, this racism
thing, it's disastrous

00:51:23.730 --> 00:51:27.475
that in 21st century, every
day there's a shooting.

00:51:27.475 --> 00:51:29.350
I think this has been
happening all the time.

00:51:29.350 --> 00:51:33.040
Only now because of cell phones
and Facebook it's out there

00:51:33.040 --> 00:51:33.880
and everybody knows.

00:51:33.880 --> 00:51:37.690
I think it's been happening
right through, all right?

00:51:37.690 --> 00:51:39.680
At one time, it was
happening legally.

00:51:39.680 --> 00:51:42.430
Now it's been
happening illegally.

00:51:42.430 --> 00:51:45.870
Now, these kind of
things are happening

00:51:45.870 --> 00:51:50.570
because we're using our
intellect to fix the problem.

00:51:50.570 --> 00:51:52.990
You're using a knife to stitch.

00:51:52.990 --> 00:51:55.220
This is not going to work.

00:51:55.220 --> 00:51:56.720
You just live that way.

00:51:56.720 --> 00:51:59.930
Whichever way you live,
your children will grasp it,

00:51:59.930 --> 00:52:03.650
and they'll make a sense out
of that in their own way.

00:52:03.650 --> 00:52:05.980
And maybe they'll fall
this way or that way

00:52:05.980 --> 00:52:08.076
because you are not the
only influence upon them.

00:52:08.076 --> 00:52:08.950
You better know that.

00:52:08.950 --> 00:52:10.850
You're going to be a mother.

00:52:10.850 --> 00:52:11.700
You must know this.

00:52:11.700 --> 00:52:14.290
You are not the only influence.

00:52:14.290 --> 00:52:16.992
There are all kinds of
people, and there's Google.

00:52:16.992 --> 00:52:20.928
[LAUGHTER]

