AUDIENCE: Saghguru, you talked
about identity and inclusive

00:52:27.610 --> 00:52:28.760
consciousness.

00:52:28.760 --> 00:52:30.730
So I want to know, let's
say like you talked

00:52:30.730 --> 00:52:33.100
about the sensory
body and feeling

00:52:33.100 --> 00:52:35.750
that everyone is part
of you kind of thing.

00:52:35.750 --> 00:52:38.480
So where does the role
of action come in?

00:52:38.480 --> 00:52:42.320
So if I do something, do
I identify myself with it

00:52:42.320 --> 00:52:43.230
what I did?

00:52:43.230 --> 00:52:45.160
And let's say if I
feel that you are

00:52:45.160 --> 00:52:48.770
or everyone is part of like
me or the whole cosmos,

00:52:48.770 --> 00:52:50.150
and you do something.

00:52:50.150 --> 00:52:52.490
Is you doing something,
cosmos doing something,

00:52:52.490 --> 00:52:53.340
me doing something?

00:52:53.340 --> 00:52:55.165
Where does the action
come in the picture?

00:52:57.472 --> 00:52:59.596
SADHGURU: See, this is the
beauty of our existence.

00:53:03.180 --> 00:53:05.530
In this existence,
in this cosmos,

00:53:05.530 --> 00:53:07.760
we are not even a speck of dust.

00:53:07.760 --> 00:53:09.500
That small we are.

00:53:09.500 --> 00:53:13.200
But still, creation has
given as an individuality,

00:53:13.200 --> 00:53:17.940
an individual nature that we
can experience these things.

00:53:17.940 --> 00:53:21.810
But countless number of people
who lived on this planet

00:53:21.810 --> 00:53:23.430
before you and me came.

00:53:23.430 --> 00:53:24.270
Where are they?

00:53:24.270 --> 00:53:25.810
They're all topsoil.

00:53:25.810 --> 00:53:28.230
They've become part of
the Earth, isn't it?

00:53:28.230 --> 00:53:30.980
So if you get it
from me today, you

00:53:30.980 --> 00:53:33.805
can transform your life,
that really everything

00:53:33.805 --> 00:53:35.930
is a part of you, and you
are a part of everything,

00:53:35.930 --> 00:53:38.900
not as a thought,
but experientially.

00:53:38.900 --> 00:53:41.110
If you can experience
everything around you

00:53:41.110 --> 00:53:44.560
as you experience the 5,
10 fingers of your hands,

00:53:44.560 --> 00:53:47.820
then you will see life becomes
tremendously beautiful.

00:53:47.820 --> 00:53:52.170
Otherwise, anyway one day you
will get it from the maggots.

00:53:52.170 --> 00:53:54.570
But it will be a
bit too late lesson.

00:53:54.570 --> 00:53:58.110
But everybody will get
it one day, isn't it?

00:53:58.110 --> 00:53:59.650
Hello?

00:53:59.650 --> 00:54:01.200
When people bury
us, we are going

00:54:01.200 --> 00:54:03.420
to get the point that we
are part of the Earth.

00:54:03.420 --> 00:54:05.450
Right now, we forget it.

00:54:05.450 --> 00:54:07.240
We can live sensibly.

00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:10.780
So this must come
from an experience.

00:54:10.780 --> 00:54:13.100
If you come from a
thought, again you're

00:54:13.100 --> 00:54:16.780
thinking how is inclusiveness
and individuality existing

00:54:16.780 --> 00:54:17.930
at the same time?

00:54:17.930 --> 00:54:20.500
That is the beauty
of this existence.

00:54:20.500 --> 00:54:24.000
It is the filth which has
become the flower, isn't it?

00:54:24.000 --> 00:54:26.830
Yes or no?

00:54:26.830 --> 00:54:30.330
It is the filth which
has become the flower.

00:54:30.330 --> 00:54:33.260
In your mind filth is
different, flower is different,

00:54:33.260 --> 00:54:37.210
but in existence filth
and flower are same.

00:54:37.210 --> 00:54:41.220
They are not different, just
different ways of existing.

00:54:41.220 --> 00:54:44.930
For you nose, filth
doesn't feel good.

00:54:44.930 --> 00:54:48.390
But if you were a pig,
you would like the filth.

00:54:48.390 --> 00:54:50.100
Nothing wrong with that.

00:54:50.100 --> 00:54:52.510
Because it's the same thing.

00:54:52.510 --> 00:54:54.550
It's the same thing or no?

00:54:54.550 --> 00:54:56.310
Hello?

00:54:56.310 --> 00:54:58.280
It's the same thing, isn't it?

00:54:58.280 --> 00:55:01.180
It is just that in our mind
and with our intellect,

00:55:01.180 --> 00:55:03.430
we are breaking everything.

00:55:03.430 --> 00:55:06.290
This breaking is only a
psychological reality.

00:55:06.290 --> 00:55:08.510
This is not existentially true.

00:55:08.510 --> 00:55:11.360
See, we started a huge movement
called Project GreenHands.

00:55:11.360 --> 00:55:15.275
I think something a little
bit was there in this.

00:55:15.275 --> 00:55:17.080
This happened like this.

00:55:17.080 --> 00:55:21.970
When I saw that entire southern
India was turning into desert

00:55:21.970 --> 00:55:24.710
very rapidly, rivers
were drying up,

00:55:24.710 --> 00:55:27.310
ground water went from
like 100, 150 feet

00:55:27.310 --> 00:55:31.270
to almost 1,500
feet and palm trees,

00:55:31.270 --> 00:55:35.030
the crowns were falling off, we
thought we must do something.

00:55:35.030 --> 00:55:37.000
Then I did this to them.

00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:40.020
One day I called-- I
went to a small village

00:55:40.020 --> 00:55:41.400
and called for people.

00:55:41.400 --> 00:55:43.890
About 5,000 people turned up.

00:55:43.890 --> 00:55:46.880
So I made them-- this is around
11 o'clock in the morning.

00:55:46.880 --> 00:55:50.370
The weather is not like
this in southern India.

00:55:50.370 --> 00:55:53.050
It's hot, summer sun.

00:55:53.050 --> 00:55:54.280
I made them sit there.

00:55:54.280 --> 00:55:58.040
Close by, there were
about five rain trees,

00:55:58.040 --> 00:55:59.810
three of them really large ones.

00:55:59.810 --> 00:56:01.460
You've see rain trees?

00:56:01.460 --> 00:56:04.290
Some of them can be
as large as an acre.

00:56:04.290 --> 00:56:05.985
It's shade.

00:56:05.985 --> 00:56:08.260
So three of them are
really large ones.

00:56:08.260 --> 00:56:11.559
Two of them were medium-sized
ones, very attractive.

00:56:11.559 --> 00:56:13.100
I would love to be
under those trees.

00:56:13.100 --> 00:56:16.330
But I made them sit
here in hot sun.

00:56:16.330 --> 00:56:19.770
And I went on talking,
stretching the talk,

00:56:19.770 --> 00:56:22.649
telling them stories,
telling them jokes.

00:56:22.649 --> 00:56:24.690
They were all very
enthusiastic in the beginning.

00:56:24.690 --> 00:56:30.750
Slowly-- if you're walking
around, you won't feel the sun.

00:56:30.750 --> 00:56:35.040
If you just sit under the
sun, it just really gets you.

00:56:35.040 --> 00:56:37.034
About 1 and 1/4,
1 and 1/2 hours,

00:56:37.034 --> 00:56:38.200
they were really going away.

00:56:38.200 --> 00:56:40.880
They're thinking, what's
wrong with this Sadhguru?

00:56:40.880 --> 00:56:44.050
He's just frying us in the sun.

00:56:44.050 --> 00:56:48.760
Then I said, come, and I
took them under the tree.

00:56:48.760 --> 00:56:50.580
Ah!

00:56:50.580 --> 00:56:52.220
Everybody.

00:56:52.220 --> 00:56:56.290
Suddenly, you know
what is a tree.

00:56:56.290 --> 00:56:57.910
Otherwise you were
thinking of how

00:56:57.910 --> 00:57:01.190
to make furniture out of this.

00:57:01.190 --> 00:57:03.430
Now suddenly you
know what's a tree.

00:57:03.430 --> 00:57:07.280
I made them sit
down there and read.

00:57:07.280 --> 00:57:10.190
It's a certain spiritual
process that I set up,

00:57:10.190 --> 00:57:13.145
a process for them where I
told them, what you exhale,

00:57:13.145 --> 00:57:14.580
trees are inhaling.

00:57:14.580 --> 00:57:16.670
What they exhale,
you are inhaling.

00:57:16.670 --> 00:57:19.020
Once they experienced
it, now you

00:57:19.020 --> 00:57:20.860
can't stop them
from planting trees.

00:57:20.860 --> 00:57:23.580
They planted over
28 million trees.

00:57:23.580 --> 00:57:25.680
And you can't stop them.

00:57:25.680 --> 00:57:28.280
They changed the entire culture.

00:57:28.280 --> 00:57:33.840
But when this happened to
me about 9, 10 years ago,

00:57:33.840 --> 00:57:36.290
I went back to my [INAUDIBLE]
city, which I had not

00:57:36.290 --> 00:57:38.740
gone and done any work there,
I had never spoken there,

00:57:38.740 --> 00:57:41.160
I avoided this because
my family lives there.

00:57:41.160 --> 00:57:44.370
I wanted to be anonymous in
that town, not recognized.

00:57:44.370 --> 00:57:46.630
But because of the
Google and stuff,

00:57:46.630 --> 00:57:48.820
I got recognized everywhere.

00:57:48.820 --> 00:57:51.670
So when I went there, they
insisted I must do something.

00:57:51.670 --> 00:57:53.150
I called for a program.

00:57:53.150 --> 00:57:59.170
All kinds of people turned up,
my kindergarten school friends,

00:57:59.170 --> 00:58:03.050
teachers, my college teachers,
school teachers, everybody.

00:58:03.050 --> 00:58:04.930
When I spoke and
all this happened,

00:58:04.930 --> 00:58:07.860
and my English teacher came up
to me from school and she said,

00:58:07.860 --> 00:58:10.150
now I understand
why you wouldn't

00:58:10.150 --> 00:58:12.360
let me teach Robert Frost.

00:58:12.360 --> 00:58:15.050
I said, ma'am, why would
I not let you teach Frost?

00:58:15.050 --> 00:58:17.450
I like Frost.

00:58:17.450 --> 00:58:19.600
I have some poetry
in his own voice.

00:58:19.600 --> 00:58:20.770
I said I like Frost.

00:58:20.770 --> 00:58:22.320
Why would I not let you teach?

00:58:22.320 --> 00:58:23.220
Don't you remember?

00:58:23.220 --> 00:58:25.650
You didn't let me teach Frost.

00:58:25.650 --> 00:58:26.490
Then I remembered.

00:58:26.490 --> 00:58:28.750
One day she came up,
and we were always

00:58:28.750 --> 00:58:32.080
studying English poems
and English literature.

00:58:32.080 --> 00:58:35.320
Suddenly she introduced
this American poet and said,

00:58:35.320 --> 00:58:36.210
this is Robert Frost.

00:58:36.210 --> 00:58:36.920
He's a great guy.

00:58:36.920 --> 00:58:38.475
And she started out
the poem. "Woods

00:58:38.475 --> 00:58:40.220
are lovely, dark and deep."

00:58:40.220 --> 00:58:41.543
I said stop.

00:58:41.543 --> 00:58:43.810
[LAUGHTER]

00:58:43.810 --> 00:58:47.200
I said, a man who
calls a tree a wood,

00:58:47.200 --> 00:58:49.480
I'm not going to have
anything to do with this guy.

00:58:49.480 --> 00:58:50.420
[LAUGHTER]

00:58:50.420 --> 00:58:52.010
She said, no, no,
Robert Frost is

00:58:52.010 --> 00:58:54.700
a great-- I don't care
who the hell he is.

00:58:54.700 --> 00:58:57.211
He calls tree a wood.

00:58:57.211 --> 00:58:58.710
I'm not going to
listen to that guy.

00:58:58.710 --> 00:59:00.640
I didn't let her teach.

00:59:00.640 --> 00:59:04.070
We chose Longfellow instead of
Frost because I didn't let her

00:59:04.070 --> 00:59:07.020
teach Frost that year/

00:59:07.020 --> 00:59:12.750
So I'm saying if you call a
tree a wood, it's a commodity.

00:59:12.750 --> 00:59:15.500
This water, this Earth
that you walk upon,

00:59:15.500 --> 00:59:17.780
the people that you see,
these are not commodities.

00:59:17.780 --> 00:59:20.130
This is life, isn't it?

00:59:20.130 --> 00:59:22.740
The air that you breathe,
the water that you drink,

00:59:22.740 --> 00:59:25.940
the soil that you walk upon,
the trees that you sit under,

00:59:25.940 --> 00:59:30.510
everything else in this world
is life and life-making material

00:59:30.510 --> 00:59:32.420
for you.

00:59:32.420 --> 00:59:35.520
If you forget this, you
will treat it as commodity.

00:59:35.520 --> 00:59:38.290
If you experience this,
that this is actually

00:59:38.290 --> 00:59:40.360
what is making
your life, then you

00:59:40.360 --> 00:59:44.890
will see the most fantastic
thing about this universe.

00:59:44.890 --> 00:59:46.400
Everything is one,
but everything

00:59:46.400 --> 00:59:48.100
is separate at the same time.

00:59:48.100 --> 00:59:50.270
That's what gives
us an experience.

00:59:50.270 --> 00:59:52.020
That's why I can sit
here and talk to you.

00:59:52.020 --> 00:59:53.400
Otherwise, how to talk to you?

00:59:58.270 --> 01:00:00.672
JONATHAN BERENT: Maybe
one more question.

01:00:00.672 --> 01:00:01.630
AUDIENCE: Hi, Sadhguru.

01:00:01.630 --> 01:00:03.000
Thank you for coming.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:05.980
So for me, one way to
achieve inclusiveness

01:00:05.980 --> 01:00:10.290
is to see other
people as ourselves.

01:00:10.290 --> 01:00:12.080
For example, right
now I know for sure

01:00:12.080 --> 01:00:16.310
that you exist within me,
because your voice happens

01:00:16.310 --> 01:00:18.333
within my head, your image.

01:00:18.333 --> 01:00:19.200
SADHGURU: No, no no.

01:00:19.200 --> 01:00:20.940
If voices are happening
within your head,

01:00:20.940 --> 01:00:22.550
it means something else.

01:00:22.550 --> 01:00:26.820
[LAUGHTER]

01:00:26.820 --> 01:00:29.510
AUDIENCE: So your image
happens within me,

01:00:29.510 --> 01:00:31.530
because it reflects
through my eyes and--

01:00:31.530 --> 01:00:33.863
SADHGURU: You mean to say you
have nightmares every day?

01:00:33.863 --> 01:00:36.310
[LAUGHTER]

01:00:36.310 --> 01:00:42.350
AUDIENCE: Well, so my point
is, I see you within me.

01:00:42.350 --> 01:00:44.690
That I know for sure.

01:00:44.690 --> 01:00:49.500
But I wonder whether you
see me within you as well.

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:52.480
And if you answer
yes or no, then that

01:00:52.480 --> 01:00:57.590
may be a belief, because
how do I know it's true?

01:00:57.590 --> 01:01:00.950
SADHGURU: See, there are
two levels of reality here.

01:01:00.950 --> 01:01:03.240
There is a
psychological reality,

01:01:03.240 --> 01:01:06.660
and there's an
existential reality.

01:01:06.660 --> 01:01:09.590
Existential reality
is not your making.

01:01:09.590 --> 01:01:12.800
Psychological reality
is entirely your making.

01:01:12.800 --> 01:01:15.120
But a large part of it
is unconsciously made,

01:01:15.120 --> 01:01:18.700
so you believe it is real.

01:01:18.700 --> 01:01:22.400
Whatever is true in your
psychological reality

01:01:22.400 --> 01:01:25.100
may have some social
relevance but has

01:01:25.100 --> 01:01:27.420
no existential relevance.

01:01:27.420 --> 01:01:31.750
Right now, if I say you are
within me, you will feel good.

01:01:31.750 --> 01:01:33.912
If I say I love you,
you'll feel good.

01:01:33.912 --> 01:01:34.870
Maybe it's true for me.

01:01:34.870 --> 01:01:35.990
Maybe it's true for you.

01:01:35.990 --> 01:01:39.170
But it's not floating
around anywhere here, OK?

01:01:39.170 --> 01:01:41.720
It's just my emotion
and your emotion.

01:01:41.720 --> 01:01:45.060
Yes, it is nice that
our emotions are sweet,

01:01:45.060 --> 01:01:47.390
our thoughts are sweet,
our actions are sweet.

01:01:47.390 --> 01:01:49.810
It's wonderful if it is so.

01:01:49.810 --> 01:01:54.840
But it has only psychological
and social relevance.

01:01:54.840 --> 01:01:57.430
It has no existential relevance.

01:01:57.430 --> 01:01:59.780
If you want to
know life, you have

01:01:59.780 --> 01:02:04.620
to step out of this bubble
called psychological reality

01:02:04.620 --> 01:02:07.250
and step into
existential reality.

01:02:07.250 --> 01:02:09.850
Then only you have
a taste of life.

01:02:09.850 --> 01:02:14.150
Otherwise, you are just a bundle
of thoughts, emotions, ideas,

01:02:14.150 --> 01:02:20.940
opinions, and now I'm there in
there in all that. [CHUCKLING]

01:02:20.940 --> 01:02:25.070
So what I would tell
all of you is instead

01:02:25.070 --> 01:02:29.120
of thinking about it,
instead of analyzing it,

01:02:29.120 --> 01:02:32.060
an experiential
dimension has to happen.

01:02:32.060 --> 01:02:38.020
If you're willing to dedicate
28 to 30 hours of focused time,

01:02:38.020 --> 01:02:40.700
we will give you tools
with which you can

01:02:40.700 --> 01:02:42.860
make this happen for yourself.

01:02:42.860 --> 01:02:45.310
This is not some empty talk.

01:02:45.310 --> 01:02:49.200
This has happened to
millions of people.

01:02:49.200 --> 01:02:51.180
This has worked.

01:02:51.180 --> 01:02:54.510
And I must tell you,
first 21 years of my work,

01:02:54.510 --> 01:02:57.770
as a rule I never
appeared in the media.

01:02:57.770 --> 01:02:59.510
Of course, I didn't
have a website.

01:02:59.510 --> 01:03:03.860
I never put up one poster or
banner or even a brochure.

01:03:03.860 --> 01:03:06.740
Only by word of mouth
millions of people came.

01:03:06.740 --> 01:03:08.630
Obviously it must
have worked for them

01:03:08.630 --> 01:03:10.540
to bring their
family and friends.

01:03:10.540 --> 01:03:13.490
And now I'm not
promising any miracle.

01:03:13.490 --> 01:03:15.300
I'm not taking you to heaven.

01:03:15.300 --> 01:03:18.730
I'm telling you the source
of all your problems is you,

01:03:18.730 --> 01:03:20.910
not somebody else.

01:03:20.910 --> 01:03:22.860
I'm saying it's hard talk.

01:03:22.860 --> 01:03:26.306
It is not some miraculous
promise of going to heaven,

01:03:26.306 --> 01:03:27.930
some La-La land is
there and everything

01:03:27.930 --> 01:03:29.000
will be fine for you.

01:03:29.000 --> 01:03:29.810
No.

01:03:29.810 --> 01:03:33.860
In spite of that, people
came, because they

01:03:33.860 --> 01:03:36.080
saw the transformation
within themselves.

01:03:36.080 --> 01:03:38.140
And people around
them had to come.

01:03:38.140 --> 01:03:39.560
There was no other way.

01:03:39.560 --> 01:03:43.870
So I'm saying this is the
technology of well-being.

01:03:43.870 --> 01:03:48.110
We are handling our external
well-being in a scientific way

01:03:48.110 --> 01:03:50.600
through many means
of technology.

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:53.470
Why is it that we
are so crippled when

01:03:53.470 --> 01:03:55.260
it comes to our interiority?

01:03:55.260 --> 01:03:57.880
We are trying to handle
it through our emotions.

01:03:57.880 --> 01:04:00.350
We are trying to handle it
through our philosophies.

01:04:00.350 --> 01:04:02.710
We are trying to handle
it through our ideologies

01:04:02.710 --> 01:04:04.480
and belief systems.

01:04:04.480 --> 01:04:08.730
No, it's time you approach
this human mechanism

01:04:08.730 --> 01:04:11.730
in a scientific manner,
how to make this

01:04:11.730 --> 01:04:15.260
into a full-fledged possibility.

01:04:15.260 --> 01:04:18.490
See, every life in
this world is only

01:04:18.490 --> 01:04:20.550
trying to become a
full-fledged life,

01:04:20.550 --> 01:04:22.890
whether it's a worm
or an insect or a bird

01:04:22.890 --> 01:04:24.450
or an animal or a tree.

01:04:24.450 --> 01:04:28.530
All they're striving for
is to become full-fledged.

01:04:28.530 --> 01:04:30.650
But we know what is
a full-fledged worm.

01:04:30.650 --> 01:04:32.350
We know what is a
full-fledged insect.

01:04:32.350 --> 01:04:34.150
We know what is
full-fledged everything.

01:04:34.150 --> 01:04:37.450
But we do not know what is
a full-fledged human being.

01:04:37.450 --> 01:04:40.540
Because even if I make you the
king or queen of this planet

01:04:40.540 --> 01:04:44.830
tomorrow, still you will ask
[INAUDIBLE] for the stars.

01:04:44.830 --> 01:04:46.770
Because there is
something within you

01:04:46.770 --> 01:04:49.360
which is longing to
become in finite.

01:04:49.360 --> 01:04:51.370
If you are longing
for the infinite,

01:04:51.370 --> 01:04:53.760
you can't go about
conquering space.

01:04:53.760 --> 01:04:55.620
It's not going to get you there.

01:04:55.620 --> 01:04:58.985
The finiteness to you has
come to you only because

01:04:58.985 --> 01:05:01.890
of your identification
with your physicality.

01:05:01.890 --> 01:05:03.710
Because the nature
of physicality

01:05:03.710 --> 01:05:05.640
is a defined boundary.

01:05:05.640 --> 01:05:09.230
Without a defined boundary,
there is no physical nature.

01:05:09.230 --> 01:05:12.140
But is it true that
this physical body

01:05:12.140 --> 01:05:14.090
you slowly accumulated?

01:05:14.090 --> 01:05:15.090
Is it true?

01:05:15.090 --> 01:05:17.470
Or were you born like this?

01:05:17.470 --> 01:05:18.760
You accumulated this.

01:05:18.760 --> 01:05:21.140
What you accumulate
can be yours.

01:05:21.140 --> 01:05:23.520
It can never, ever be you.

01:05:23.520 --> 01:05:26.160
Or in other words, you
are living your life

01:05:26.160 --> 01:05:30.900
without experiencing the life
that you are even for a moment.

01:05:30.900 --> 01:05:34.890
Your entire involvement is with
your physiology and psychology.

01:05:34.890 --> 01:05:37.610
It's time it changes,
that you experience

01:05:37.610 --> 01:05:39.180
the life that you are.

01:05:39.180 --> 01:05:42.480
This life that you are
doesn't come with boundaries.

01:05:42.480 --> 01:05:44.070
It's only the body.

01:05:44.070 --> 01:05:48.117
It is boundaries, and you
must stick to the boundaries.

01:05:48.117 --> 01:05:48.950
It's very important.

01:05:48.950 --> 01:05:51.740
Don't expand it too much.

01:05:51.740 --> 01:05:52.610
Thank you very much.

01:05:52.610 --> 01:05:54.485
JONATHAN BERENT: Thank
you so much, Sadhguru.

01:05:54.485 --> 01:05:55.240
[APPLAUSE]

01:05:55.240 --> 01:05:57.660
Thank you.

01:05:57.660 --> 01:05:59.550
Thank you all.

